FBIS4-31696 "dreeu115_b_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-115 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 BULGARIA Second Reactor at Kozloduy Plant Restarted Second Reactor at Kozloduy Plant Restarted AU1506101994 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 0900 GMT 15 Jun 94 AU1506101994 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network Bulgarian BFN [Text] The 440-megawatt second reactor at the Kozloduy Nuclear Plant was restarted and connected to the country's grid. It is expected that by the end of the day it will be functioning at 50 percent of its capacity. The reactor was switched off for three months, during which time it was repaired and refueled. Three additional reactors are functioning at a total capacity of 1,400 megawatt. The plant's fourth and fifth reactors are being repaired.
